						               													<description>Rakpoka is an easy to learn seven card poker card game for &amp;#10;two or more players aged 8 to adult.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Unlike poker there is no bluffing or gambling involved in the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play is on a Rakpoka mat using two traditional decks of playing cards (including jokers) in tile form.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player, in turn selects and lays combinations of traditional poker hands in a crossword fashion in order to secure the highest possible score.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(Score charts are printed on each corner of the play mat).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scores can be doubled, trebled, quadrupled or quintupled by laying hands over Bonus Squares (labelled x2, x3, and x4).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you have ever played Scrabble, you will pick this up very quickly....&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules booklet can be found on our website.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
